caverns throughout the region.Though they won’t be easy to find.
You may need to fulfil a condition...I seem to remember an old reading
about RELICANTH and WAILORD.Maybe you should visit places with
those Pokémon in your party?Please show me the legendary titans.
I’ll have a reward waiting for you.

24.text1:
Steven: Ah, yes, that’s them.
The legendary titans!You truly are a legendary Trainer.
In every sense of the word.Your REGISTEEL in particular...
It’s very beautiful, isn’t it?As promised, here’s a reward.
The ancient artifacts of Hoenn!

25.text1:
Steven: In Hoenn, legends say the
battle between GROUDON and KYOGRE\x25BDis what shaped the lands and seas.But then the Pokémon that rules the
skies, known as RAYQUAZA, came down\x25BDand halted the battle.Each of those Orbs I gave you has a
connection with one of those Pokémon.Perhaps fate will allow you to meet
them for yourself.Hmm...An underground cave, filled with a
large amount of water...A heated mountain, surrounded by
lava and molten rock...A place that stretches into the sky,
where only powerful Trainers gather...If you were to visit places like that...
You may just be able to find them.

26.text1:
Steven: Thank you for all of your help
in satisfying my unusual requests.Oh, I never got your name, did I?
...But I won’t ask for it this time.Our fun will have to wait for the
right time.

27.text1: BATTLE

28.text1: Steven: A battle?\rI won’t deny that you’re a very\ninteresting Trainer.\rSadly, as you are now...\nYou wouldn’t stand a chance.

29.text1: Steven: A battle?\nWith the Champion of the Sinnoh region?\rI’ll gladly accept such an offer.\rIf you’re going to mount a serious\nchallenge...\rPrepare for the worst!\r

30.text1: Steven: You...\nYou’ve become very strong.\rFufufu.\nI hope we can battle again.

43.text1:
You! Kid!Behind me is the one, the only,
Team Galactic Eterna Building!You can see it on the sign, yeah?
It’s no place for a kid like you.You don’t have a Forest Badge either,
so your Pokémon must be weak!We don’t want them, either!

44.text1:
You! Kid!You have the Forest Badge from the
Pokémon Gym here?Then your Pokémon must be plenty
strong, yeah?Then they’ll be perfect for
Team Galactic!I’ll be taking them now!

45.text1: These Pokemon are very strong...\rWait, was I meant to collect weak\nPokémon instead?\rIs this kid planning to raid our\nbuilding and take the Pokémon back?\rI must inform Commander Jupiter...\r

46.text1:
Hi! I’m Gardenia!
I’m this town’s Gym Leader!I don’t know about you, but I’m
crazy about Grass-type Pokémon!Say, could I ask you for a favour?Would you be able to show me a
Grass-type Pokémon called SNOVER?If you leave Eterna to the east, you
can get to Route 216 via Mt. Coronet.There’s loads of wild SNOVER there.
I can’t really go myself, though...If you can do that for me,
I’ll let you challenge my Gym!

47.text1:
Gardenia: Say, could I ask you for a
favour?Would you be able to show me a
Grass-type Pokémon called SNOVER?If you leave Eterna to the east, you
can get to Route 216 via Mt. Coronet.There’s loads of wild SNOVER there.
I can’t really go myself, though...If you can do that for me,
I’ll let you challenge my Gym!

48.text1:
Hey, there!
How’s it going, Champ-to-be?Sorry to disappoint you after you’ve
come such a long way, but...The Gym Leader, Gardenia, isn’t here
at the moment.Gardenia went over to Route 216 to
look for some Grass-type Pokémon.I’m sure she’d come back to the Gym
if you go and talk to her.Route 216 is to the northeast of
here, through Mt. Coronet.Incidentially, you’ll likely find plenty
of Ice-type Pokémon in Route 216.As an exclusive tip from me to you...
The Pokémon in this Gym hate Ice-types!

20.text1: Hello, Trainer!\nI have a dream.\rCould you help my CLEFAIRY\nlearn Dazzling Gleam?

22.text1: CLEFAIRY learned\nDazzling Gleam!\r

23.text1: Ah! My dream has been realized!\nThank you ever so much, Trainer!

24.text1: Someone, somewhere, saw that you\nmade somebody’s wish come true.

25.text1: Oh...\rYou can’t teach my CLEFAIRY\nDazzling Gleam?\rOr you simply don’t want to?\rSigh...\nWill my CLEFAIRY ever sparkle?

28.text1: Ah! My dream has been realized!\nThank you ever so much, Trainer!\r

7.text1:
Oh, what’s that? You already own
this exact bicycle?Hah! Looks like your mother has some
good taste in vehicles!Then, I’ll let you have this rare stone
my CLEFAIRY found instead!
It’s a PORYGON!\nIt seems to have been abandoned...\rIt appears eager to join your team.\nWill you take PORYGON with you?

8.text1: PORYGON looks sad...

9.text1: You have no room for Pokémon!\rPORYGON looks sad...

10.text1: \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000 adopted the PORYGON!\r

11.text1: Do you want to give a nickname to\nthis PORYGON?

16.text1: Two trainers have made a pact!\nA Covenant Orb is formed!

6.text1:
Oak: Do you know the names of any
other Pokémon professors, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000?I can assure you there are many more
than just myself and Professor Rowan!Elm, Birch, Juniper, Sycamore, Kukui...All of these names belong to fellow
Pokémon professors around the world!

7.text1:
Oak: I should inform you that my full
name is Professor Samuel Oak.I have a cousin in Alola who is known
as Professor Samson Oak!His research focuses on the regional
variants found in Alola.Did you know that the Vulpix in Alola
are Ice-type, rather than Fire-type?

8.text1:
Oak: I have a grandson called Blue.He was the Champion of the Kanto
Pokémon League, in fact.Though only for a brief time.
Then he lost to his rival, Red.At least Blue found a place as the
Viridian City Gym Leader!Though he’s often away from it,
causing trouble for challengers.That boy...

9.text1:
Oak: Oh, yes. I once had a protégé who
very much enjoyed outdoor research.His name is Professor Willow.
He used to study Pokémon under me.Him and his assistants are always
making strides in Pokémon research!

10.text1:
Oak: Have you ever thought of yourself
as a photographer, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000?I once invited a talented young man
to take photos of Pokémon in their\x25BDnatural habitat.It was a place called Pokémon Island...
And what a beautiful place it was!The young photographer helped me
with completing my Pokémon Report!

11.text1: Oak: Hm! That one is CHARMANDER!\nYou shoud raise it patiently.\rSo, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000, you’ve claiming the\nFire-type Pokémon CHARMANDER?

12.text1: \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000 received the CHARMANDER\nfrom Professor Oak!\r

13.text1: Oak: Ah! You already have six Pokémon\nwith you.\rYou’ll have to store a Pokémon in\na PC box first!

14.text1: Do you want to give a nickname to\nthis SQUIRTLE?

15.text1: Do you want to give a nickname to\nthis BULBASAUR?

16.text1: Do you want to give a nickname to\nthis CHARMANDER?

17.text1:
Oak: Ah, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000, it’s you.Are the Pokémon I gave you
doing well?They’re the Pokémon species that
Trainers receive as their first\x25BDpartner in the Kanto region.It’s always exciting to see what
each Trainer picks for their journey!

18.text1:
Oak: Oh! You want to know about the
legendary Pokémon of the world?There certainly are a lot of stories.
Some which have been proven true.The legendary birds of Kanto.
The legendary beasts of Johto.There’s many, many, many more.
But not all Trainers can face them!If you encounter a legendary Pokémon,
please do tell me.It will be the proof we need that
you’re worthy of their presence.

19.text1: Oak: Ah, it’s you! Good to see you!\nWhat can I help you with, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000?

20.text1: POKéDEX

21.text1: LEGENDARIES

22.text1: CANCEL

23.text1: Oak: I’ll be staying here for a while.\nDo drop by if you need anything!

24.text1:
Oak: What’s this?!You went to the Distortion World and
battled with the legendary GIRATINA?!Remarkable. Truly remarkable!
This is absolutely unprecedented!At any rate, you are indeed worthy of
meeting Legendary Pokémon, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000!I’m positive they would appear before
you if you go to the right place.Please ask me about anything that
you would like to know.

25.text1: GENERAL

27.text1: NOTHING

28.text1:
Oak: You want to know about the
legendary birds of Kanto?Well then. Let’s see...
There are three of them in all.ARTICUNO, the titan of ice.
It likes snowy, mountainous areas.ZAPDOS, the titan of electricity.
Electricity attracts its attention.MOLTRES, the titan of fire.
It’s said to await strong Trainers.When these three come together...
The guardian of the sea will arise.At least, that’s what the legends say.But it’s impossible to test it unless a
Trainer can capture all three birds!They’re all extremely rare Pokémon,
even within the Kanto region.Who knows if they can even be found
in Sinnoh?

29.text1:
Oak: You want to know about the
legendary beasts of Johto?Well then. Let’s see...
There are three of them in all.Legends say they represent the events
that destroyed the Brass Tower in the\x25BDJohto region’s Ecruteak City.RAIKOU represents the lightning strike
which ignited the flames.ENTEI represents the flames that
then scorched the Brass Tower.SUICUNE represents the rains that
quenched the raging flames.They are also said to be Pokémon that
were resurrected after perishing in\x25BDthe Brass Tower tragedy.They were resurrected by a Pokémon
known as the guardian of the skies.As for where they could be found...
I would look around for high ground.Perhaps the Rock Climb technique
you have could prove useful?

30.text1:
Oak: Take a look at the two feathers
I have here, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000.They’re both known as Clear Wings.
You might think they look ordinary...But these feathers have a puzzle that
I’m currently trying to solve.They may have a connection to the two
Pokémon known as the guardians of the\x25BDsea and sky.LUGIA, the guardian of the sea, is
said to mediate between the three\x25BDlegendary birds of Kanto.Maybe this Clear Wing would react to
ARTICUNO, ZAPDOS and MOLTRES?If you were to go somewhere very cold,
somewhere that generates electricity,\x25BDand somewhere where Trainers gather...Well, it would be an amazing encounter
to see any of them, that’s for sure!

31.text1:
Oak: What’s this? In your party...
ARTICUNO, ZAPDOS and MOLTRES?!Now that is incredible!
Thank you, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000.Now, this Clear Wing...
Will it react, I wonder?

33.text1:
Oak: Ah, splendid! It really did work!
This Clear Wing has changed.It’s now a deep silver colour...
And it’s sparkling, too.It must be the Silver Wing!Thanks for your assistance, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000.
I’d like you to have this Silver Wing.

34.text1: Oak: Do you know of anywhere in the\nsea surrounded by small islands?\rPerhaps you’d somehow find LUGIA there\nif you carry the Silver Wing with you.\r

35.text1:
Oak: Now, this other Clear Wing...
Perhaps it could be the Rainbow Wing?The guardian of the sky was said to
have resurrected three Pokémon.RAIKOU, ENTEI and SUICUNE.
The legendary beasts of Johto.I’m sure this Clear Wing would respond
to the presence of those Pokémon!I would imagine those Pokémon would
enjoy high places...Maybe the Rock Climb technique could
help you find them?If you somehow catch all three...
Please show them to me.

36.text1: Oak: In your party...\nRAIKOU, ENTEI, and SUICUNE?!\rYou’ve done it again, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000!\nTruly impressive!\rNow, let’s see if this Clear Wing...\rOh?!\r

37.text1:
Oak: Excellent! This Clear Wing is now
a sparkling, vibrant rainbow colour!This is clearly the Rainbow Wing!
How very exciting!\v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000, thank you again.
I’d like you to have this, too.

38.text1:
Oak: A tall place where the departed
are given due respect...There is a place like that in Sinnoh,
is there not?Taking a Rainbow Wing to a place like
that might allow you to meet HO-OH,\x25BDthe sky guardian.

39.text1: Oak: I can’t thank you enough for your\nhelp with my research, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000.

40.text1:
Oak: Ah, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000!
What fantastic timing.I was hoping you could meet me soon on
Route 224, east of the Pokémon League.I have a letter here with instructions
on what I’d like your help with.Here you go!

41.text1: Oak: Once again, that’s Route 224.\nPlease visit when you can.

48.text1:
Excuse me, are you a Trainer?You are? Lovely!I have several fossils here that some
of my colleagues have collected from\x25BDthe tunnels underground.There’s a machine in Oreburgh’s
museum that can revive the Pokémon\x25BDin these fossils.Would you be willing to take the fossils
over there? They’ll know what to do.

49.text1: Lovely! There’s three of each.\nExcept for the rare Old Amber.\rThere’s a lot of fossil types here,\nso please bear with me...\r

50.text1: The reason I’m asking is because\nI really want to see an AERODACTYL.\rIf you can show me one, then I’ll give\nyou another gift for your trouble!

51.text1:
Ah... Well, I can’t force you.But you are carrying a Pokédex and
collecting data on Pokémon, right?Reviving these fossils would help fill
several pages in that, too.You can’t find these fossilized
Pokémon in the wild!

52.text1:
Wow! That’s an AERODACTYL with you!You must have revived it from an
Old Amber at the musem, right?It looks super strong! In fact,
I have the perfect TM for it!Please, take it as a thank you
gift for showing me AERODACTYL.

53.text1:
The Champion of the Kanto and Johto
regions owns an AERODACTYL, too.His AERODACTYL is also able to use
the Rock Slide move in battle.Over there, though, everyone thought
AERODACTYL couldn’t use the move!Luckily, all AERODACTYL can definitely
use Rock Slide these days!Anyway, thank you! I’m really glad that
I got to see AERODACTYL in person.

54.text1:
Hey! Trainer!
Hey, listen!If you’re here, I bet you like
to dig around underground, right?Did you know your Pokémon can
Dig underground as well?You can teach them how to with this
Technical Machine! Here!

55.text1: That isn’t all Dig is good for!\rIt lets the user dodge an opponent’s\nmove, then strike back at their\x25BDopponent on the next turn!

56.text1: Don’t forget! You don’t need an\nEscape Rope when you can use Dig!

13.text1: Hello, \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000!\rYou’ve kept your Renegade Platinum\nsave from an earlier version, yes?\rLet’s get your save ready for v1.1.0.\nJust a moment, please...\r

3.text1: Hello! You’re a Trainer, aren’t you?\rOh, your Pokémon look hurt.\nLet me heal them for you...\r

4.text1: Aaron: Brilliant! Here come my nasty,\nmean, yet beautiful partners!\r

5.text1: Aaron: Really? I’d reconsider.\rI’ll make it worth your while,\nand it’s fine if you lose.\rSo, shall I show you my beautiful\nbugs in an unofficial battle?

6.text1: Aaron: Ha! That was fun.\rDon’t sweat about losing.\nI’m an Elite Four member, after all!\r

7.text1: Aaron: Wow! Your Pokémon are\ntrained seriously well.\rI expect I’ll see you at the\nPokémon League for an official battle!\r

8.text1:
So, have I shown you the greatness
of Bug-type Pokémon?Either way, I’ve got a TM for you
for listening to my spiel!It’s the purely offensive Bug-type
move, X-Scissor!

9.text1:
Your name is \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000?I’m Aaron of the Elite Four.
It’s good to meet you.I’m a huge fan of Bug-type Pokémon.
They’re nasty-mean, and yet beautiful.Do you get what I mean?
Some of them are really strong, too.I just can’t help but gush about
them to everyone!In fact, how about I show you some
beautiful bugs right now?I’ll try and fight closer to your level,
but don’t worry if you lose!So, shall I show you my beautiful
bugs in an unofficial battle?

10.text1: Aaron: Alright! It was great to meet\nyou. See you another time!\r

3.text1: Help! Help!\r

4.text1: I must inform everyone in the hope\nthat we receive aid...\r

5.text1:
\v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000: Woah! That was a surprise!The Pokémon Mansion is that huge
building on Route 212, yeah?Weirdly dressed thugs... Does she
mean those strange Team Galactic guys?Those goons must have decided
they want something from there...I’m off then!
To help a lady in distress!

6.text1: Weirdly dressed thugs have taken\nover the Pokémon Mansion!\r

9.text1:
Bebe: Sorry to be so sudden. I’ve
had that Up-Grade for a while now,\x25BDbut I’ve never had a use for it.It’s great for any PORYGON--otherwise
known as the Virtual Pokémon!I don’t have a partner PORYGON,
unfortunately.A PORYGON will evolve into PORYGON2
if it gets exposed to that Up-Grade.

4.text1:
Argh! Ow!
That hurts!I was adding some boiling water to the
pot to prepare it for Poffin making,\x25BDand I spilt it all over me!Do you have a Burn Heal?
It’d be really useful right now...

5.text1: You don’t... That’s too bad.\nThen I should get some cold water...

6.text1:
Ah! That’s much better.
Thank you very much.In fact, I can do more than just
give thanks!Here’s a Technical Machine--one that’ll
put a Pokémon in the same situation!

7.text1: Scald is a Water-type move that\nshoots boiling water at the opponent.\rPokémon won’t be hurt as badly as\nI was, but that move can still leave\x25BDa nasty burn on its target!

8.text1: Oh, fantastic!\nLet me just apply it...\r

25.text1: Keira: Take this Accessory, too!\r

14.text1: The presence of The Original One\ncan be felt everywhere, my child.\rNever forget that it is always looking\nover you, in everything that you do.

15.text1: The Fairy-type...\rA Plate for The Original One to\ngain the power of the moon.\rSuch an item has never been\nfound in Sinnoh.

16.text1: Ah... These old bones are tired.\nI need a long, rejuvenating rest.\rI wish I could Rest like a Pokémon...\rYou are a Trainer, are you not?\rYou can let your Pokémon take\na well deserved Rest with this TM...\r

17.text1: The Original One...\nDo you think it ever needs to Rest?

19.text1:
The Fairy-type...
It is blasphemous!They say a Pixie Plate exists in the
Kalos and Alola regions, but we have\x25BDseen nothing of that sort here.It must be lies! Nothing but lies!
Lies, lies, lies, lies, lies!

20.text1:
The Original One is said to have a
move called Judgment.The Original One releases countless
shots of light of any type it wishes.It’s undoubtedly an all-powerful move.
Could anything withstand that power?

21.text1:
Have you ever heard of the
Plate items?There are sixteen in all, each one
representing a specific type.The Original One is said to be able to
change its type by equipping a Plate.There’s no Normal-type Plate, though.There hasn’t been any sign of a
Fairy-type Plate in Sinnoh, either.

22.text1:
The Hall of Origin...It is said that the Hall of Origin is
the home of The Original One.We believe it exists in the sky above
the very peak of Mt. Coronet.That is why we observe the mountain
peak on the stained glass window.

23.text1: Did you know that the Plate items are\nnot one-of-a-kind?\rRumours say that they can be found by\ndigging in the Underground.

24.text1:
Greetings, child.Welcome to this place of worship for
that which we call the Original One.It is the creator of both our land and
the Pokémon found within legends.Mere weaklings like us cannot hope
to ever meet the Original One...You’d have to be the Champion to even
stand a chance of being worthy.Nevertheless, we continue to offer
our gratitude for its blessings.

25.text1:
Oh, goodness... 
You’re the new Champion, aren’t you?Perhaps, child, you could be the one
to finally meet the Original One.But first, you must prove that you
have mastery over all Pokémon types!

26.text1:
There are sixteen Type Master trainers
around Sinnoh, each possessing a Plate.Defeat them using the same type in a
one-on-one battle to win the Plate.If you gather all sixteen of the
Original One’s Plates, return here!

27.text1:
All sixteen Plates are indeed currently
in your possession...Excellent work, young Champion.But I am afraid that your challenge
does not end here.The Original One is the creator of all.
You must understand what all means.

28.text1:
You must journey to the Spear Pillar
at the peak of Mt. Coronet.If you are truly the one who is fated
to meet with the Original One...Then it will undoubtedly respond to
the sound of the Azure Flute.

29.text1:
Your Pokédex is worthy of a diploma.
Very well done, young Champion.As you have proven yourself worthy,
I shall bequeath this to you.The ancient relic known only as the
Azure Flute!

30.text1:
...You have a Pokédex, do you not?
Yes, that will prove yourself nicely.Complete that Pokédex!
It should be worthy of a diploma!Only then will you be worthy to
meet the Original One!

45.text1:
Hey there!
How’s it going, Champ-to-be?Sorry to say that the Gym Leader
is away from the Gym at the moment.Wake--Crasher Wake, rather--said he
was heading out west to Route 212,\x25BDto enjoy the scenery for a while.Maybe you can ask him to return
to the Gym if you can find him?

47.text1: TORCHIC seems extremely peckish...\nIt may want an Old Gateau.\r

56.text1: Ooh! Look at that SHARPEDO!\nIt’s the meanest fish I’ve ever seen!\r

57.text1: Woah! You have a GYARADOS!\nHey, Trainer, is GYARADOS a fish?\rI don’t know, but I love it!\nIt’s the meanest thing I’ve ever seen!\r

58.text1: Yay! Thank you, Trainer!\nI’ll tell my sister all about it!\r

59.text1: Thanks a bunch, Trainer!\nI can’t wait to tell my sister!

8.text1: Your Poison-type looks pretty strong!\rShould we find out who has the\nultimate Poison-type Pokémon?

10.text1: Oh, wow.\rIt seems the ultimate Poison-type\nPokémon belongs to you!\rThat means you are the rightful owner\nof this precious item!\r

11.text1: The ultimate Poison-type Pokémon\nbelongs to me!\rBut I’m always ready for another\nPoison-type battle.

4.text1: You should listen to your elders!\nYou don’t know what you’re missing!

5.text1:
Splendid!As you can likely see from my clothing
and demeanor, I come from a wealthy\x25BDbackground.I was fortunate to be born into a
wealthy family, and enjoyed a wide\x25BDrange of experiences as a result.One thing that I especially enjoyed
as a young girl was Surfing.I was gifted a darling LAPRAS by
my father, and we were able to\x25BDtake to the seas as we pleased.There’s no sad end to this tale, but
at my age, I cannot continue such\x25BDactivities, fun as they are.However, LAPRAS love to cross the sea
with people and Pokémon on its back.Which brings me to my point, and the
reason for telling you this tale...

6.text1: Could I entrust my LAPRAS to you,\nso it can cross the seas once more?

7.text1: Oh, goodness...\nWas telling that tale a waste?

8.text1: Oh, goodness...\nYou have too many Pokémon.

9.text1: Oh, goodness...\nThat’s a relief. Thank you.\r

10.text1: \v0103ぁ\x0000\x0000 accepted the LAPRAS!\r

11.text1: Would you like to give a nickname\nto the LAPRAS you received?

12.text1: I do miss Surfing the seas...\nIt was very exhilarating.\rPlease take good care of LAPRAS.
